'''肉卷'''（英語：Meatloaf），又名烘肉卷，是用[[絞肉|絞肉]]及其他[[香料|香料]]所製成的[[美國|美式]]家常菜<ref name="zeldes">{{Cite web | last = Zeldes | first = Leah A. | title = Eat this! Meatloaf, easy comfort | work = Dining Chicago | publisher = Chicago's Restaurant & Entertainment Guide, Inc. | date = 2009-09-02 | url = http://www.diningchicago.com/blog/2010/06/30/eat-this-meatloaf-easy-comfort/ | format =  | doi =  | accessdate = 2010-08-03 | archive-date = 2011-10-11 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20111011211536/http://www.diningchicago.com/blog/2010/06/30/eat-this-meatloaf-easy-comfort/ | dead-url = no }}</ref>，其起源可以追溯至[[歐洲|歐洲]]，類似的菜式早於公元5世紀的[[古羅馬飲食文化|古羅馬]]烹飪書《{{link-en|阿匹西尤|Apicius}}》（{{lang|en|''Apicius''}}）中已有記載，傳統的肉卷在[[德國|德國]]及[[比利時|比利時]]都頗受歡迎，製作方法亦與荷蘭的[[肉丸|肉丸]]有點近似。現代美式烘肉卷的[[菜譜|菜譜]]至19世紀才出現<ref name="Meatloaf history">{{Cite web |url=http://www.buzzle.com/editorials/1-2-2006-85269.asp |title=Meatloaf history in US |access-date=2015-07-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140108213315/http://www.buzzle.com/editorials/1-2-2006-85269.asp |archive-date=2014-01-08 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>据传由[[賓夕凡尼亞州|賓夕凡尼亞州]]的[[德裔美國人|德裔美國人]]手中改良得來<ref name="zeldes" />。在[[經濟大蕭條|經濟大蕭條]]期間，肉卷成為不少美國家庭的廉價[[蛋白質|蛋白質]]來源。

